The "Artistic License"

Preamble

The intent of this document is to state the conditions under which a Package
may be copied, such that the Copyright Holder maintains some semblance of
artistic control over the development of the package, while giving the users
of the package the right to use and distribute the Package in a more-or-less
customary fashion, plus the right to make reasonable modifications.

Definitions

"Package" refers to the collection of files distributed by the Copyright
Holder, and derivatives thereof.

"Copyright Holder" is whoever is named in the copyright or copyright notice
for the package.

"You" and "your" refer to each licensee under this agreement.

"Reasonably" means in a manner that would be considered reasonable by a
prudent person. Compliance does not require unanimous consent, but rather a
consensus of prudent parties.

"Freely Available" means that no fee is charged for the item, and that the
item is available for re-distribution at no cost.

"Freely Distributable" means the same as Freely Available.

1. Artistic License 2.0

   (a) Definitions

       i. "Copyright Holder" means the individual(s) or organization(s)
          named in the copyright notice for the entire Package.

       ii. "Contributor" means any party that has contributed code or other
           material to the Package, in accordance with the Copyright Holder's
           procedures.

       iii. "You" and "your" refers to each individual or legal entity
            exercising rights granted by this License.

       iv. "Package" refers to the collection of files distributed by the
           Copyright Holder, and derivatives thereof.

       v. "Modification" refers to any addition to or deletion from the
          substance or structure of either the Package itself or any
          Derivative Work of the Package, but does not include changes or
          additions to any files that are explicitly excepted by the Package.

       vi. "Derivative Work" refers to any work that is based on (or derived
           from) the Package, including but not limited to any modifications
           thereto.

   (b) Permission for Use and Modification

       i. You are permitted to use this Package in source form, compiled form,
          or in either form, provided that you comply with all of the terms
          and conditions of this License.

       ii. You may make modifications to the source code of this Package or
           Derivative Works.

   (c) Distribution of Modified Versions

       i. If you modify this Package, you may distribute the modified Package
          under the same terms as the original Package, provided that you:

          - Make the modified Package available to the Copyright Holder at no
            cost;
          - Document the nature of the modifications;
          - Retain all copyright and license notices; and
          - Include a notice stating that the Package has been modified.

   (d) You may distribute binary forms of this Package or Derivative Works
       provided that you:

       i. Include the same copyright and license notices and disclaimers as
          the original Package, in the same locations;
       ii. Ensure that all documentation associated with the binary form
           makes clear that any modifications have been made; and
       iii. Ensure that all documentation and other notices carried with the
            binary form clearly state the origin and copyright of the Package.

2. It is not permitted to place the Package under any other license.

3. If you make modifications to this Package, you may distribute the modified
   Package under the same terms as this License, as long as you comply with
